define({"topics":[{"title":"Minimum viable documentation for APIs","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Minimum viable documentation set (MVD) is the smallest amount of documentation needed so that the majority of developers willingly adopt an API, just enough that they don't feel overwhelmed by frustration or give up because the API wastes their time.<\/p>","href":"topics\/minimum-viable-docset_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"minimum-viable-documentation-for-apis"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"minimum-viable-documentation-for-apis-d203e106","topics":[]},{"title":"The API reference docs: Are yours complete?","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The largest and most important part of the reference collection is the section that describes all of the API endpoints.<\/p>","href":"topics\/basic-reference_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"the-api-reference-docs-are-yours-complete"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"the-api-reference-docs-are-yours-complete-d203e117","topics":[]},{"title":"Example reference entry","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The following is a reference entry for one endpoint on a fictional API. This is just one way to represent all the necessary information.<\/p>","href":"topics\/reference-example-container_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"example-reference-entry"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"example-reference-entry-d203e128","topics":[]},{"title":"Provide a description for everything that needs one","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Descriptions comprise the most important part of the spec. Documentation calls for effective descriptions and it requires an effort to include the descriptions in every place where one can be included.<\/p>","href":"topics\/swagger-reference_2.html","menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"tocId-d203e139","topics":[]}]});